Wesley L. SISCHO, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden United States Penitentiary Annex, Fort Leavenworth, Kansas, Appellee. No. 1643. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 13, 1938. Wesley L. Sischo, pro se. Summerfield S. Alexander, U. S. Atty., and Homer Davis, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS, and BRATTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment appealed from is affirmed on authority of Watkins v. Zerbst, 10 Cir., 85 F.2d 999 and Blockburger v. United States, 284 U.S. 299, 52 S.Ct. 180, 76 L.Ed. 306.
